<subSubSection box="[198,1358,792,819]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,677,1708]" box="[198,1358,792,819]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,792,818]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
I-Leg- 
<number box="[409,422,793,819]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="6.0">6</number>
greatly expanded at distal end; excretory pore surrounded by a sclerotized ring.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,677,1708]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,351,831,857]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Description.</emphasis>
Female: Integument net shaped. Postoculare on large rounded plates (
<figureCitation box="[1171,1266,832,858]" captionStart="FIGURE 2 A – C" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[206,1383,197,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,197,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2 A – C. Sperchon schwoerbeli sp. nov., female: A = idiosoma, dorsal view; B = palp, medial view; C = I-Leg- 4 - 6. Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/188052/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[1226,1242,832,858]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
A
</figureCitation>
). Two anterior pairs of dorsocentral plates (Dc- 
<number box="[534,544,870,896]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
and - 
<number box="[610,626,870,896]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
) fused and lying laterally; other 
<number box="[1011,1026,870,896]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="3.0">3</number>
pairs of dorsocentral plates (Dc- 
<number pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3- 5</number>
) occupy central position.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,677,1708]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Anterior coxae lying close to each other, but not fused (
<figureCitation box="[889,960,948,974]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1550,1574]" captionTargetBox="[356,1227,189,1515]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[342,1245,175,1535]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sperchon schwoerbeli sp. nov., female: idiosoma, ventral view. Scale bar = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/188051/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[948,960,948,974]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A); anterior margins of Cx- 
<number box="[1310,1320,948,974]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
concave, apodemes weakly developed. Posterior groups of coxae widely separated; glandularia Cxgl- 
<number box="[1229,1243,986,1012]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="4.0">4</number>
at antero-lateral margin of Cx- 
<number box="[323,337,1025,1051]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="3.0">3</number>
; L between anterior end of first coxae and posterior end of fourth coxae 
<number box="[1199,1247,1025,1051]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="506.0">506</number>
. Vgl- 
<number box="[1318,1328,1025,1051]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
reduced, only accompanying setae on very small sclerites. Excretory pore surrounded by sclerotized ring; one pair of ventral plates; postgenital sclerite developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,677,1708]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Genital field lying between posterior coxae; L of genital valves 
<number box="[992,1042,1141,1167]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="206.0">206</number>
; genital valves not covering the genital acetabula; posterior acetabula more or less rounded; L of acetabula 
<number box="[1050,1099,1180,1206]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
: 
<number box="[1111,1143,1180,1206]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="78.0">78</number>
- 
<number box="[1152,1184,1180,1206]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="78.0">78</number>
- 
<number box="[1193,1224,1180,1206]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="53.0">53</number>
. Chelicera L 
<number box="[1384,1431,1180,1206]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="328.0">328</number>
, basal segment L 
<number box="[349,396,1218,1244]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="231.0">231</number>
, claw L 
<number box="[495,527,1218,1244]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="98.0">98</number>
, L basal segment/claw 
<number box="[801,841,1218,1244]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.4">2.4</number>
; palp total L 
<number box="[995,1042,1218,1244]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="931.0">931</number>
, dL and %L (in parentheses): P- 
<number box="[1425,1435,1218,1244]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
<number box="[151,180,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="43.0">43</number>
(
<number box="[197,238,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="4.6">4.6</number>
), P- 
<number box="[286,300,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
<number box="[308,352,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="209.0">209</number>
(
<number box="[368,424,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="22.4">22.4</number>
), P- 
<number box="[473,486,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="3.0">3</number>
<number box="[494,538,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="270.0">270</number>
(
<number box="[555,588,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="29.0">29</number>
), P- 
<number box="[636,650,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="4.0">4</number>
<number box="[658,702,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="347.0">347</number>
(
<number box="[718,774,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="37.3">37.3</number>
), P- 
<number box="[823,836,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="5.0">5</number>
<number box="[844,873,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="62.0">62</number>
(
<number box="[890,931,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="6.7">6.7</number>
); L P- 
<number box="[1005,1019,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
/P- 
<number box="[1054,1068,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="4.0">4</number>
<number box="[1076,1116,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="0.6">0.6</number>
; P- 
<number box="[1156,1170,1257,1283]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
with long ventrodistal projection bearing one long seta and one short seta (
<figureCitation box="[770,863,1296,1322]" captionStart="FIGURE 2 A – C" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[206,1383,197,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,197,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2 A – C. Sperchon schwoerbeli sp. nov., female: A = idiosoma, dorsal view; B = palp, medial view; C = I-Leg- 4 - 6. Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/188052/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[825,841,1296,1322]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
B
</figureCitation>
); P- 
<number box="[912,926,1296,1322]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="4.0">4</number>
ventral margin with 
<number box="[1176,1191,1296,1322]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
short peg-like setae, area with peg-like setae subdivides P- 
<number box="[594,608,1334,1360]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="4.0">4</number>
into 
<number box="[669,684,1334,1360]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="3.0">3</number>
unequal parts, distal part longer than proximal or median parts.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,677,1708]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
I-Leg- 
<number box="[273,287,1373,1399]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="6.0">6</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[304,396,1373,1399]" captionStart="FIGURE 2 A – C" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[206,1383,197,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,197,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2 A – C. Sperchon schwoerbeli sp. nov., female: A = idiosoma, dorsal view; B = palp, medial view; C = I-Leg- 4 - 6. Scale bars = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/188052/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[360,375,1373,1399]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
C
</figureCitation>
) greatly expanded at distal end, greatest H of I-Leg- 
<number box="[1023,1037,1373,1399]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="6.0">6</number>
<number box="[1045,1093,1373,1399]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="106.0">106</number>
; fourth legs with a few short setae, none of which are plumose. Claw with weakly protruding claw blade and 
<number box="[1119,1134,1412,1438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
clawlets. L of I-Leg: 
<number pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="9.1116150247213232E16">91, 116, 150, 247, 213, 234</number>
; L of IV-Leg: 
<number box="[599,881,1450,1476]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.56131163331325E14">156, 131, 163, 331, 325</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,677,1708]" box="[197,389,1489,1515]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Male: unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,677,1708]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,339,1527,1553]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Discussion.</emphasis>
The greatly expanded I-Leg- 
<number box="[692,706,1528,1554]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="6.0">6</number>
is a unique character of the new species which separates the present species from all known members of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,677,1708]" box="[197,1012,1605,1631]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,337,1605,1631]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after Professor Jürgen Schwoerbel.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,677,1708]" box="[197,825,1643,1670]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,300,1643,1669]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Habitat.</emphasis>
Discovered in mosses in a mountain stream.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,1182,1682,1708]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,677,1708]" box="[197,1182,1682,1708]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,350,1682,1708]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Distribution</emphasis>
. Known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[625,675,1682,1708]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">type</typeStatus>
locality in Himachal Pradesh State (
<collectingCountry box="[1103,1169,1682,1708]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">India</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
